%% Data Flow Diagram: vllm-orchestrator-gateway
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client<br/>(OpenAI-compatible)
    participant Gateway as vllm-orchestrator-gateway<br/>8090/TCP HTTP
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8085/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors<br/>(regex, PII, etc.)
    participant LLM as vLLM / LLM Backend

    Note over Gateway: Startup: Load config.yaml<br/>Build routes from config<br/>Initialize TLS client (if certs present)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Authorization: Bearer token<br/>Content-Type: application/json
    Note over Gateway: Resolve route name<br/>Look up configured detectors<br/>Inject detector specs into payload

    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>Authorization: forwarded<br/>x-forwarded-*: forwarded<br/>Optional mTLS client cert
    Note over Orchestrator: Process input detectors

    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run input detection<br/>(e.g., PII regex scan)
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results

    alt Input detection triggered & has fallback
        Orchestrator-->>Gateway: Detection response with results
        Note over Gateway: Fallback message configured:<br/>Replace response content
        Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>Fallback message in chat completion format
    else No input detection or no fallback
        Orchestrator->>LLM: Forward to LLM for inference
        LLM-->>Orchestrator: LLM response

        Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run output detection
        Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results

        Orchestrator-->>Gateway: Chat completion response<br/>(with detection metadata)

        alt Output detection triggered & has fallback
            Note over Gateway: Replace response content<br/>with fallback_message
            Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>Fallback message in chat completion format
        else No output detection or no fallback
            Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>Original LLM response
        end
    end
